mind-forge command line interface

Usage: mf [OPTIONS] [COMMAND]

Commands:
  source      Manage content sources
  asset       Manage project assets
  project     Manage projects
  article     Manage articles
  term        Manage terminology
  completion  Generate shell completion scripts
  build       Build articles
  publish     Publish articles
  config      Manage configuration

Options:
      --config <PATH>    
  -v, --verbose...       
  -q, --quiet            
      --format <FORMAT>  [default: text] [possible values: text, json]
      --no-color         
  -h, --help             Print help
  -V, --version          Print version
